<item>
            <title>[LU-11580] Crash after cfs_percpt_alloc when doing modprobe lnet</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11580</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;options libcfs cpu_npartitions=1 cpu_pattern=&quot;0&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0-27&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or just&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;options libcfs cpu_pattern=&quot;0&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0-27&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get a crash when loading lnet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2018-10-29T09:21:10.475881+01:00 b-an04 kernel: [ 2138.540432] LNet: HW NUMA nodes: 2, HW CPU cores: 28, npartitions: 1&lt;br/&gt;
2018-10-29T09:21:35.396884+01:00 b-an04 kernel: [ 2162.956139] BUG: unable to handle kernel paging request at ffffffffaaddd990&lt;br/&gt;
2018-10-29T09:21:35.396900+01:00 b-an04 kernel: [ 2162.963917] IP: native_queued_spin_lock_slowpath+0x16f/0x1a0&lt;br/&gt;
2018-10-29T09:21:35.396902+01:00 b-an04 kernel: [ 2162.970228] PGD 1c80e0e067 P4D 1c80e0e067 PUD 1c80e0f063 PMD 8000001c80a000e1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without any options for libcfs loading lnet works as it should.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This worked whith MOFED 3.3 and Lustre 2.7&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 18.04 (4.15.0-38)&lt;br/&gt;
MOFED 4.4</environment>
